21:40.184 --> 21:41.226
Do you know Jesus today?

21:41.286 --> 21:42.147
That's the number one thing.

21:42.568 --> 21:47.474
Without him, you will never, ever, ever, ever, ever, a zillion, ever's.

21:48.962 --> 21:50.364
experience abundant life.

21:53.188 --> 21:53.789
You can try.

21:53.829 --> 21:59.897
You can fake it, but you won't make it.

22:02.361 --> 22:12.174
Without Jesus, you can never know who you are or what your purpose is, why you're here.

22:13.036 --> 22:17.682
You will never experience strength and protection and preparation.

22:19.938 --> 22:21.240
You won't have the good shepherd.

22:22.481 --> 22:31.091
You'll be the sheep wandering about without any direction in constant danger with no hope.

22:35.416 --> 22:36.037
Well, that's huge.

22:38.700 --> 22:43.285
Now, I would say for most of you, maybe all of you here today, you know the good shepherd.

22:45.307 --> 22:47.570
So, check, you got that one.

22:48.578 --> 22:50.721
But what can you do to draw closer to Him?

22:50.981 --> 22:53.825
Because look at that next part, verse nine again, look at verse nine again.

22:53.865 --> 23:00.114
I am the door, if anyone comes, anyone enters by me, he will be saved.

23:01.055 --> 23:02.337
Okay, that was the first point.

23:03.178 --> 23:04.019
Gotta have Jesus.

23:04.800 --> 23:08.925
Second, and they'll go in and out and find pasture.

23:12.751 --> 23:14.032
We're called to go in and out.

23:15.234 --> 23:18.258
A relationship with Jesus Christ, the abundant life with Jesus,

23:18.370 --> 23:25.520
is not only does it involve us coming into the good shepherd's presence, but it involves us going out.

23:27.963 --> 23:33.631
Both are necessary for 2026 in your life, going in.

23:33.651 --> 23:40.881
In other words, focusing in on your relationship with Christ, but also going out.

23:44.066 --> 23:47.090
You know, I was at the Dallas Expo Center.

23:47.170 --> 23:49.172
a couple of months ago.

23:49.232 --> 23:57.240
And I was in the center looking at what we were there visiting about a show and something and pay to get in, you know, and it's kind of cool.

23:58.262 --> 24:01.425
And I forgot something I left in the car.

24:02.326 --> 24:06.991
And I was at the back of the Expo Center and I saw a door that goes out.

24:07.011 --> 24:14.098
I thought, I'll just go out that door and come right back in after I go to the car.

24:16.354 --> 24:24.767
And I went out and the door closed and I turned around and there's no handle on the door on the outside.

24:24.807 --> 24:26.109
I'm out.

24:29.455 --> 24:30.657
That's a bad feeling, isn't it?

24:32.139 --> 24:41.033
To go into some place or out of some place and you turn around and you can't go the other way, you know, oh, that's not what I wanted to do.

24:43.617 --> 24:44.338
You shut out.

24:45.346 --> 24:53.758
I want you to understand that one thing that we're really good at going in to Jesus as Christians and believers, because who doesn't want to do that?

24:53.839 --> 24:55.421
Who doesn't want to get to know the good shepherd?

24:57.244 --> 25:02.832
But we forget that that door is for us to go in and out.

25:03.252 --> 25:04.855
Now I'm not talking about relationship.

25:05.436 --> 25:10.583
I'm talking about we should be thinking about how to go out.

25:14.269 --> 25:15.250
Outreach.

25:15.426 --> 25:18.831
evangelism, serving the community.

25:19.211 --> 25:31.067
However you want to put it, if you only go in and if it's all about getting in and get closer to Jesus and all your goals and your spiritual life are, I'm going to read my Bible more.

25:31.467 --> 25:31.908
Great.

25:33.070 --> 25:34.171
I'm going to pray more.

25:34.552 --> 25:35.353
You should.

25:35.413 --> 25:40.580
I'm going to worship with God's people more regularly.

25:41.901 --> 25:42.742
All good goals.

25:43.624 --> 25:45.426
They should be on your list.

25:45.890 --> 25:52.978
That handles the going in, but I want you to know that going in only is unhealthy.

25:54.920 --> 26:00.306
If you go into a place that you don't go out of, that's called prison, I'm pretty sure.

26:03.750 --> 26:06.973
And some people live the Christian life like they're in prison.

26:08.575 --> 26:11.218
Please, sir, can I have a little more food?

26:12.546 --> 26:16.010
We live our pitiful lives, hoping that God throws us a blessing.

26:19.253 --> 26:23.057
I'm going to just pray and read my Bible, go to church.

26:25.340 --> 26:34.450
And the church, instead of becoming an outpost of God's kingdom work, becomes a prison for debilitated saints.

26:39.395 --> 26:42.258
It's going out that the sheep find pasture.

26:43.330 --> 26:46.775
It's going out that the sheep find the still waters.

26:47.115 --> 26:50.600
It's when you go out that you experience your purpose.

26:51.101 --> 26:56.628
It's going out that we have participation in what God is doing among us.

26:57.830 --> 26:59.412
It's giving, not just getting.

26:59.693 --> 27:02.036
It's risking, not restricting.

27:02.076 --> 27:06.262
It's serving, not just being served.

27:10.107 --> 27:12.210
Out means you go out.

27:12.674 --> 27:13.515
into the world.

27:15.537 --> 27:25.568
If your relationship with God is centered only in your church, only in your heart, love you God.

27:30.774 --> 27:32.435
If you love me, you'll get out.

27:33.997 --> 27:35.659
What kind of sheep?

27:35.919 --> 27:38.682
God's counting sheep out in the meadow, out in the pasture.

27:38.983 --> 27:40.664
And there's one missing, it's you.

27:40.704 --> 27:42.226
You're back at the church.

27:42.402 --> 27:43.984
You're back at the fold.

27:44.264 --> 27:45.345
You're just sitting there.

27:48.529 --> 27:48.729
Out.

27:49.830 --> 27:50.711
Get out.

27:50.991 --> 27:52.813
We'll come back here tonight.

27:53.815 --> 27:57.859
But right now, you need to be out in the pasture, but there's still waters.

27:58.159 --> 28:01.123
You need to be out exercising, getting the sun.

28:01.483 --> 28:04.606
You need to be out and about doing the work of God.

28:04.907 --> 28:07.129
Yes, there are valleys, people.

28:07.450 --> 28:08.831
Yes, there are enemies.

28:09.192 --> 28:10.433
Yes, there are challenges.

28:10.753 --> 28:11.474
That's life.

28:11.874 --> 28:18.544
But we have the promise of Psalm 23 from the good shepherd whose name is Jesus.

28:19.926 --> 28:20.907
I will be with you.

28:23.731 --> 28:24.793
I will give you the strength.

28:25.654 --> 28:28.619
The good shepherd leads us, goes first.

28:31.142 --> 28:41.778
So along with your goals, your spiritual goals to pray more and read your Bible more and come to church regularly, those probably should be for all of us.

28:43.234 --> 28:45.136
have out goals too.

28:45.196 --> 28:50.141
I'm gonna give more of my money to the church.

28:50.281 --> 28:53.224
I'm gonna give more of my time to serving the Lord.

28:53.544 --> 28:55.647
I'm gonna make some new friends this year.

28:55.727 --> 28:56.928
I'm gonna share my faith.

28:57.528 --> 29:00.872
I'm gonna start adding service projects to my schedule.

29:00.932 --> 29:10.962
I'm gonna start plugging into something new and I'm gonna get out there into a world and experience the abundant life that God has for me.

29:13.442 --> 29:21.393
This here in church is great, but it's not just this that makes abundant life.

29:23.517 --> 29:25.119
Your abundant life is out there.

29:25.179 --> 29:30.286
This is the fold where we come.

29:30.326 --> 29:34.152
We find security and safety and we learn more about God and we draw closer to Him.

29:34.192 --> 29:37.977
But friends, we need to get out.

29:39.760 --> 29:41.202
So, Pastor Eric asks you,

29:41.538 --> 29:42.679
What did you do last year?

29:42.699 --> 29:43.980
What did you celebrate?

29:44.040 --> 29:45.722
What were the blessings that God gave you?

29:46.202 --> 29:47.424
Awesome.

29:47.444 --> 29:48.004
That's great.

29:48.925 --> 29:56.693
What I'm saying is on the new Sunday of the new year, what are you doing to get in and out?

29:58.094 --> 30:02.798
What an amazing blessing that our Lord gives us.

30:04.240 --> 30:06.982
He doesn't just bring you in and hold you hostage.

30:08.104 --> 30:09.245
He says, I'm the door.

30:09.505 --> 30:10.706
You come in and you go out.

30:11.490 --> 30:12.732
That's called freedom, I think.

30:15.636 --> 30:16.297
I'll protect you.

30:16.337 --> 30:17.078
I'll watch over you.

30:17.098 --> 30:18.340
I'll provide everything you need.

30:18.440 --> 30:19.262
Go on.

30:20.604 --> 30:21.705
Live the abundant life.

30:24.189 --> 30:24.810
Thank you, Lord.

30:26.252 --> 30:26.953
I think I will.

30:29.056 --> 30:29.878
You want to give it a go?

30:29.918 --> 30:32.361
You can nod.

30:32.782 --> 30:35.466
You know, even if you're not, you want to give it a go?

30:35.506 --> 30:38.470
If you want to give it a go, let's get some goals set.

30:40.013 --> 30:40.914
Go home today.

30:41.058 --> 30:44.622
Get some goals set in goals and out goals.

30:45.984 --> 30:46.324
All right?

30:47.266 --> 30:50.890
And you will find a blessing beyond anything you can say.

30:51.871 --> 30:52.352
Let's pray.

30:53.233 --> 31:10.834
Father, we're just so grateful that you're a God who gives us that freedom, who allows us to enjoy not only coming into the sheep in, but also going out into the meadow where we can run and enjoy and experience life with all the abundance that you've set before us.

31:11.042 --> 31:12.885
Lord, may you be glorified.

31:13.206 --> 31:20.658
May you be blessed by what we do and say and think this week, this day.

31:20.698 --> 31:24.204
And may we be a blessing to others as well.

31:25.506 --> 31:29.192
Father, to you be the glory, it's in Jesus' name we pray.

31:29.933 --> 31:30.354
Amen.

